title: Good Omens Opening Title - David Arnold (TV Series Official Soundtrack )
author: Silva Screen Records
comment:
Me: watches all of Good Omens in the span of two days
Me: finds this and listens to it
Me: "Oh, bebop."
The start sounds like a merry-go-round breaking down which is all the more applicable since their secret world can't keep spinning forever
I the nicest way possible, this sounds like Aziraphale falling down a flight of stairs with Crowley laughing at him

Aziraphale's bit: heavenly singing, delightful violin plucking and romantic music: 0:51 - 1:24
CROWLEY'S BIT: POUNDING PERCUSSION, MISCHEVIOUS VIOLIN, CAN PRACTICALLY HEAR HIM SAYING "DO IT WITH STYLE": 1:25 - 2:11
i never skipped the intro, it is such a good soundtrack and show, i really enjoyed it very much :)
